# Typography System Guidelines

## Always Use the Typography Component

Use the [Typography component](mdc:src/components/Typography.tsx) for all text elements instead of raw HTML tags or Tailwind text classes.

## Typography Variants

### Display Text (Hero Headlines)
```tsx
<Typography variant="display" size="9xl">Hero Headline</Typography>
<Typography variant="display" size="6xl">Large Display</Typography>
<Typography variant="display" size="3xl">Medium Display</Typography>
```

### Headings (SEO Optimized)
```tsx
<Typography as="h1" variant="heading" size="4xl">H1 Heading</Typography>
<Typography as="h2" variant="heading" size="2xl">H2 Heading</Typography>
<Typography as="h3" variant="subheading" size="xl">H3 Subheading</Typography>
```

### Body Text
```tsx
<Typography variant="body" size="base">Regular paragraph text</Typography>
<Typography variant="lead" size="lg">Lead paragraph text</Typography>
<Typography variant="large" size="xl">Large text for subheadings</Typography>
```

### Utility Text
```tsx
<Typography variant="small" size="sm">Small text for metadata</Typography>
<Typography variant="caption" size="xs">Caption text with tracking</Typography>
```

## Key Principles

1. **Semantic HTML**: Use the `as` prop to specify the HTML element (h1, h2, p, etc.)
2. **Visual Hierarchy**: Combine `variant` (semantic meaning) with `size` (visual size)
3. **Consistent Spacing**: The component handles margins automatically based on variant
4. **Accessibility**: Proper heading hierarchy and semantic markup
5. **Design System**: All typography follows the refined Apple-level design principles

